Here’s the ideal keyword criteria you should aim for 👇

🔥 Ideal Keyword Metrics (Semrush Cheat Sheet)
1. 🎯 Intent (MOST IMPORTANT)

Always prioritize:

Commercial (C) → ready to buy
Transactional (T) → wants action

✅ Examples:

“best invoicing software for freelancers”
“buy billing software philippines”
“invoice generator online”

❌ Avoid (unless for blog strategy):

Informational (e.g. “what is invoice”)
2. 📊 Volume
Sweet spot: 100 – 5,000/month

Why:

Too low (<50) → no traffic
Too high (>10k) → too competitive

👉 For your SaaS:

200–2,000 = GOLD keywords
3. ⚔️ KD % (Keyword Difficulty)
Ideal: 0 – 40%
Best range: 10 – 30%

Why:

Lower KD = faster ranking
Especially important since you're still growing authority
4. 💰 CPC (Cost Per Click)
Ideal: $0.50 – $10+

Why:

High CPC = buyer intent
Businesses are paying = money keyword

🔥 Example:

“invoicing software” ($5 CPC) → strong intent
“how to invoice” ($0.10 CPC) → weak intent
5. 🔍 SERP Features (Opportunity Check)

Look for:

Low competition in:
Featured snippet (easy to steal)
Few ads
Weak domains ranking

Avoid:

Dominated by big brands (QuickBooks, Stripe, etc.)
6. 📅 Updated / Trend
Prefer:
Stable or rising keywords
Avoid:
Dying trends
